---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/tools';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About WorkspaceLux — Office Lighting Calculators & Guides"
  description="WorkspaceLux provides free office lighting calculators and guides to help you estimate lux, lumens, LED wattage, and color temperature for offices and desks."
  path="/about"
>
  <article class="max-w-site mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 prose-content">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-main mb-4">About WorkspaceLux</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-3xl">
        Office lighting calculators and workspace lighting guides — plan lux, lumens, wattage, and color
        temperature without complex lighting design software.
      </p>
    </header>

    <h2>What WorkspaceLux is</h2>
    <p>
      WorkspaceLux is a tool-focused website that helps you plan office and workspace lighting with clear
      numbers: how bright a room or desk should be (lux), how much light output to shop for (lumens),
      roughly how much LED power that implies (watts), and which color temperature fits the task.
    </p>

    <h2>Who we serve</h2>
    <p>
      Our tools target home office workers, small business owners, facility managers, interior designers,
      and contractors who need a fast baseline before buying fixtures or talking to a lighting
      professional. Scenarios include open offices, meeting rooms, home desks, coworking areas, and
      design studios.
    </p>

    <h2>How calculations work</h2>
    <p>
      Formulas run entirely in your browser. No accounts, no stored history, no server-side processing of
      your inputs. Office and desk calculators combine room or desk area with target lux to estimate
      lumens; lumens-to-watts uses LED efficacy presets you can adjust. Color temperature
      recommendations come from curated presets aligned with common practice.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy &amp; data</h2>
    <p>
      We do not save calculator inputs on our servers. Your entries stay on your device and are used only
      for local calculations in your browser session.
    </p>

    <h2>Estimates, not engineering sign-off</h2>
    <p>
      Results are simplified planning estimates. Real projects depend on fixture photometrics, ceiling
      height, surface reflectance, glare control, daylight contribution, controls, and local codes.
      WorkspaceLux is not a substitute for qualified lighting design or electrical engineering. Use our
      output to compare options and prepare questions for professionals — not as a final specification.
    </p>

    <h2>Content updates</h2>
    <p>
      We review and update calculators and guides as standards, LED technology, and user feedback evolve.
      If you spot an error or have a suggestion, please reach out.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions, corrections, or partnership ideas? Email us at
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`} class="text-primary hover:underline">{SITE.email}</a> or visit
      our <a href="/contact" class="text-primary hover:underline">Contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
